    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle&nbsp;</p> <p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic </strong></p> <p>Zest the <strong>lemon<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span>&nbsp;</strong></p> <p>Trim and slice the <strong>spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> finely</p> <p>Roughly break up the <strong>walnuts</strong>&nbsp;in a <strong>pestle and mortar</strong> or chop them roughly</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/blue-cheese-mushroom-linguine/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a large knob of <strong>butter&nbsp;</strong>over a high&nbsp;heat</p> <p>Once hot, add the <strong>spring onion</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>garlic</strong>, <strong>panko breadcrumbs </strong>and&nbsp;the <strong>walnuts</strong>&nbsp;and cook for 2-3 min or until brown and crispy&nbsp;</p> <p>Once browned, stir in the <strong>lemon zest</strong> and season generously with <strong>salt </strong>- this is your <strong>walnut crumble&nbsp;</strong></p> <p>Transfer it to a plate and keep the pan for later</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/blue-cheese-mushroom-linguine/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice the <strong>mushrooms</strong> into thick slices</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/blue-cheese-mushroom-linguine/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>linguine</strong>&nbsp;to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong>&nbsp;with a large pinch of <strong>salt&nbsp;</strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p> <p>Cook the linguine for 8-10 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p> <p>Once done, drain the linguine,&nbsp;<strong>reserving 300ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/blue-cheese-mushroom-linguine/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, return the&nbsp;pan to a medium heat with a large knob of <strong>butter</strong>&nbsp;</p> <p>Once hot, add the <strong>mushrooms&nbsp;</strong></p> <p>Cook for 2-3 min or until they've browned</p> <p>Add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and cook for 1 min further</p> <p>Add the <strong>shaoxing</strong>&nbsp;<strong>wine</strong> and cook 1 min further</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/blue-cheese-mushroom-linguine/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the&nbsp;reserved&nbsp;<strong>pasta water</strong> to the mushrooms</p> <p>Crumble the <strong>blue cheese</strong> into the pan and cook for 3-4 min or until the sauce has a creamy consistency, then set aside</p> <p>Cut and juice half of the <strong>lemon</strong> straight into the pan&nbsp;</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/blue-cheese-mushroom-linguine/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, finely chop the <strong>parsley,</strong> including the stalks&nbsp;</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/blue-cheese-mushroom-linguine/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Stir the parsley and linguine into the sauce (loosen with water if it is too dry)&nbsp;</p> <p>Divide the pasta between bowls, top with the walnut crumble and season with pepper</p> <p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
